         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Flottbeck ¶  15th March 1872 ¶ Dear Sir,  ¶  ¶ … ¶  ¶ In the meantime the 'Baron' honoured me with a very nice letter ¶  (half german &amp; half English) delighted that I am in the possession of the Todea...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M72.03.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Booth to Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew Directors' correspondence, vol. 139, f. 64</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Flottbeck<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Near Hamburg.</p>
               </note> 15th March 1872</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir, </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>…<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The early part of the letter discusses plants that Hooker may want and ones Booth would like to receive.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the meantime the 'Baron' honoured me with a very nice letter<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> (half german &amp; half English) delighted that I am in the possession of the <name key="Todea">Todea</name> which I shall have photographed before long so that you may see what a capital thing it is, with the 100 and more fronds. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Is it not wonderful that as soon as the sun shines upon this mass it gives a most disagreeable smell, like a corpse. To what is this owing? The Baron sends me the first page of his work 'Fragmenta phytographiae Australiae' contulit liber Baro Ferd. de &amp;c, then following about 30 lines with all the stars and memberships of this and the other world.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Volume 7, 1869 -71, has 30 lines listing M's memberships and honours on the title page. </p>
               </note> But he is anxious to enter into business with me and will do anything.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From official quarters I have now got a list of things they want for which he gets very likely 'Aquila rubra'<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Prussian Orden des Roten Adler (Order of the Red Eagle). Membership of the order, as a Knight, 3rd class, was conferred on 8 March 1876; see Wilhelm I, King of Prussia, to M, 8 March 1876.</p>
               </note> which he has not.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>…<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The remainder of the letter discusses the severe winter and its effects.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Dr Hooker</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very sincerely your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Booth</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Todea">Todea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
